                            <div class="card-body">


                                The paragraph (1) of article (8) of Law of the Sea defined the internal water as the belt of waters that are on the landward side
                                of the baseline of the territorial sea. The paragraph (1) of article (2) described that the state sovereignty extends to the air
                                space as well as its underlying seabed and subsoil. This zone includes mouth of rivers, bays and waters between islands up to a
                                limit not exceeding 12 nautical miles.
                                <br /><br />



                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>



                    <div class="card">
