                                <br /><br />
                                This sovereignty extends to the air space and covers the territorial sea as well as its underlying seabed and subsoil. According to Article (3), a state has the right to
                                establish the breadth of its territorial sea up to a limit not exceeding 12 nautical miles.
                                <br /><br />
                                The normal ties line for measuring the breadth of the territorial sea is the mean low water line along the coast. Whenever  the coasts of two states are opposite or adjacent
                                to each other, neither  a state is entitled to extend its territorial sea beyond the median line, every points on the baseline from which the territorial seas of both states
                                are measured, unless otherwise specific rules for special cases.
                                <br /><br />

                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>



                    <div class="card">
