                            </a>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseThree" class="collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordion">
                            <div class="card-body">



                                It is described sometimes as adjacent zone: This is a zone contiguous to a costal state’s territorial sea, the contiguous zone may not extend beyond 24 nautical miles from the baselines
                                from which the breadth of the territorial sea is measured, a 12 nautical miles as a contiguous zone in addition to its 12 nautical miles as territorial sea, over which a state may exerts
                                the sovereignty of customs, fiscal, immigration and pollution.
                                <br /><br />
                                Some states clAims that contiguous zone is not necessary when EEZ exist, but the fact in that EEZ cannot be fully alternative of contiguous zone in case of sufficient space; its role is
                                always vital, as EEZ only manages issues of security and safety of a costal state.
                                <br /><br />





                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>




                    <div class="card">
                        <div class="card-header backBlue d-flex justify-content-between hovertitle" data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#collapsefour">
